.TH "snd_hda_codec_eapd_power_filter" 9 "snd_hda_codec_eapd_power_filter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_codec_eapd_power_filter \- A power filter callback for EAPD
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" snd_hda_codec_eapd_power_filter
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "unsigned int power_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "nid" 12
widget NID
.IP "power_state" 12
power state to evalue
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Don't power down the widget if it controls eapd and EAPD_BTLENABLE is set.
This can be used a codec power_filter callback.
